<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Controller_Router_Route trims slashes by default, which means that on a given website, these urls are equivalent :</p>

<p>/login
/login/
/login//
//login//</p>

<p>IMHO, this is quite a non desirable behavior, as :
* It can break the layout if we use relative paths in the HTML (/login &amp; /login/ are not considered the same folder);
* Having a resource accessible via multiple urls breaks one of the basic principles for SEO.</p>

<p>We cannot override that by providing our own routes, because of the file Zend/Controller/Router/Route.php, on line 160 :
$route = trim($route, $this-&gt;_urlDelimiter);</p>

<p>I've created a thread on the official forum about this issue, but got no opinion from other users :
<a href="http://forums.zend.com/viewtopic.php?f=69&amp;t=8750">http://forums.zend.com/viewtopic.php?f=69&amp;t=8750</a></p>

